Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
time_info(25.10)                                              time_info(25.10)

Name
       time_info - Reports and tracks runtime and memory performance

Syntax
       time_info

       [-help]

       [<stage_name>]

       [-current]

       [-report]

       [-stamp]

       [-table <metric_table_id>]

       Reports and tracks runtime and memory performance.

       When  the  time_info command is used without any name, an entry for the
       stage is created in the table named as "undefined". When the command is
       used multiple times without any stage name, the stage  name  is  incre-
       mented,  for  example undefined1, undefined2, undefined3. This will en-
       sure that each stage name in the table is unique.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each time_info parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man time_info.

       <stage_name>
              Specifies the name of the stage.

       -current
              Reports the current stage.

       -report
              Reports all stages up to this point

       -stamp Creates a time stamp.

       -table <metric_table_id>
              Specifies metrics table ID to support multiple tables.

              Default: 'default'

Examples
              * The  following command shows the usage of the -current parame-
                ter:

                [DEV]innovus 4> time_info -current

                =======================================================

                CPU Runtime: 0:00:52.5

                Wall Runtime: 0:03:41

                Memory Usage: 1387.4 MBytes

                Peak Memory Usage: 1505.3 MBytes

                Current Time: 12:17:13 (Jul07)

                =======================================================

              * The following command shows the usage of -report:

                @[DEV]innovus 6> time_info -report

                Total Wall | Stage Wall | Wall % | Date -  Time      |  Memory
                | Stage

                ----------------+----------------+------------+-------------------+------------+----------------------

                0:00:00     | 0:00:00    | 0.0%   | 8:27:08 (Jul07) | 824.3 MB
                | init

                ----------------+----------------+------------+-------------------+------------+----------------------

                Number of threads: 1 * 1 (id: default)

